<subSubSection id="4D80ED1C700EA90A3123677FDB1D2161" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="3E778587FCE4BC426595291D4129AF93" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="83FE373D7BE55B1E5B228AF07CC12EC1" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
The species is named after the Latin word 
<emphasis id="94D0C56A1404E82CC8B1BA74CEDD65B6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">concavus</emphasis>
, which refers to the shallowly concave 8th male sternite.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
